don't think Max Payne uses Matrix bullet time. A trademark of the matrix was to have everything freeze or go ultra slow and have the camera move in circles around everything to get a perfect 3D view.<br>
The whole standard slow-motion aspect is a very old in movies. I can't think of any names, but Face Off used alot of slow motion and it came out before the matrix. There's also movies years before that, that created the concept.<br>
Arnold movies had a whole lot of slow motion and whatever that loud groaning 'NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO' was used in was also a slow-motion action scene. I don't think I've seen a game that uses actual 'matrix style' bullet-time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=414.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=414.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=414.topic&index=0><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.emailToFriend?topicID=414.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.threadControl?topicID=414.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=414.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=414.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rules and Regulations!<option value="polykarbon